This paper is about designing a reliable leaderboard for machine learning competitions, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of maintaining accuracy in a sequential and adaptive model, which relates to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions practical adversarial attacks, which is a topic in cybersecurity (cs.CY) and the need for limiting re-submissions, which is a concern in cryptography (cs.CR).
